HEADWORD: Trammeled
<hw>Tram"meled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Man.)</fld>
<def>Having blazes, or white marks, on the fore and hind foot of one
side, as if marked by trammels; -- said of a horse.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>trammelled</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trammeler</ent>⟦br⟧
